The paper deals with regular languages and their complexity, which falls under the category of formal languages (cs.FL). The use of combinatorial methods suggests that the paper may also be relevant to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and information theory (cs.IT). The characterization of regular languages meeting certain bounds may also be of interest to the computational complexity community (cs.CC). Finally, the mention of tight upper bounds suggests that the paper may involve some form of mathematical optimization, which could place it in the category of logic in computer science (cs.LO).
